Title: General compact quantum groups, a tutorial
Author: Tom H. Koornwinder
Comments: 33 pages
Report-no: Univ. Amsterdam Math. 94-06
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Operator Algebras; Quantum Algebra
Journal-ref: Representations of Lie groups and quantum groups, V. Baldoni & M.
  A. Picardello (eds.), Pitman Research Notes in Mathematics Series 311,
  Longman Scientific & Technical, 1994, pp. 46--128
\\
  A tutorial introduction is given to general Hopf algebras and
to general compact quantum groups. In the definition and further treatment
of compact quantum groups C*-algebras are avoided. Contact with
Woronowicz's compact matrix quantum groups is made at a later stage.
